<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424989>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Specimens of Thalictrum minshanicum (previously misidentified as T. javanicum or T. ramosum). A. China, Gansu, Wudu, P.C. Kuo 5090 (WUK, barcode unavailable). B. China, Gansu, Zhugqu, P.C. Kuo 5390 (WUK, barcode unavailable). C. China, Sichuan, Beichuan, C.L. Tang et al. 269 (CDBI0026275). D. China, Sichuan, Beichuan, C.L. Tang et al. 269 (CDBI0026276)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5424989/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424993>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Holotype sheet of Thalictrum minshanicum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5424993/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424995>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Thalictrum minshanicum in the wild (Pingwu in Sichuan, China, the type locality).A. Habitat. B. Habit. C. Roots. D. Portion of stem. E. Leaf (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). F. Leaflet (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side).G. Portion of abaxial side of leaflet. H. Flower, with the sepals having fallen. I. Sepals (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). J. Stamens. K. Carpels. L. Aggregate fruit. M. Achenes (immature)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5424995/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424997>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Distribution of Thalictrum brevisericeum var. brevisericeum, T. minshanicum, T. pseudoramosum, and T. ramosum. Arrow indicates the type locality of both T. minshanicum and T. pseudoramosum, i.e. Pingwu in Sichuan, China." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5424997/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424999>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Holotype sheet of Thalictrum brevisericeum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5424999/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425001>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Thalictrum brevisericeum var. brevisericeum in the wild (A‒F & L, M: Songxian in Henan, China; G‒K: Meixian in Shaanxi, China, the type locality).A. Habitat. B. Habit. C. Roots. D. Portion of stem. E. Leaf (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). F. Leaflet (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). G. Portion of abaxial side of leaflet. H. Flower, with the sepals having fallen. I. Sepals (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). J. Stamens. K. Carpels. L. Aggregate fruit. M. Achenes (immature)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5425001/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425003>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Specimens of Thalictrum javanicum. A. Indonesia, Java, C.L. Blume s.n. (L0038655). B. Indonesia, Java, C.A. Backer 481 (BO, barcode unavailable); inset: flower. C. Indonesia, Java, J.H. Kern 7775 (BO, barcode unavailable); inset: aggregate fruit (immature). D. Indonesia, Java, W.S. Hoover et al. Deden 83 (BO, barcode unavailable); inset: aggregate fruit." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5425003/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425005>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Holotype sheet of Thalictrum ramosum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5425005/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5425007>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Thalictrum ramosum in the wild (Jiangkou in Guizhou, China). A. Habitat. B. Habit. C. Roots. D. Portion of stem. E. Leaf (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). F. Leaflet (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). G. Flower, with the sepals having fallen. H. Sepals (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). I. Stamens. J. Carpels. K. Aggregate fruit. L. Achenes (immature)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5425007/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

